2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper discusses the application of the proposed method to motion capture data recovery, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new formulation of the matrix completion problem using a relaxation of the rank objective, which involves designing efficient algorithms for optimization. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper involves numerical optimization techniques for solving the proposed formulation of the matrix completion problem. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper involves the use of information theory concepts such as intrinsic dimension to formulate the matrix completion problem.
